scene_description_enriched: The scene depicts the martyrdom of Saint Sebastian, who is shown standing, pierced by numerous arrows, with a halo indicating his sainthood. To the left, two archers are in the process of shooting arrows at him. Behind the archers, a stone structure with arched openings reveals onlookers. The setting is an outdoor landscape with rolling hills and trees. Below the main scene, two figures, a man and a woman, are shown in prayer, framed by architectural elements. The inscription above the praying figures reads 'sancte sebastiane semper uox tua' (Saint Sebastian, may your voice always be).
